main event: Mrs. Elizabeth Wagner reported a fast-moving object in the sky that resembled a star but behaved unlike any known aircraft on September 19, 1950.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 30 minutes and exhibited rapid directional changes, Mrs. Wagner initially believed it to be a celestial body, The sighting was reported to the USAF, It was noted that the object followed an airline path without blinking lights, The report suggested it could have been a probable aircraft sighting, but no conclusive evidence was found.
witness description: a couple living in Elba, New York
